rimitives — see the Radix UI documentation for their props."],[46,"`AvatarFallback` renders when the image is unavailable — typically the user's initials."],[47,"`AvatarGroup` stacks several avatars into an overlapping row."],[69,"`BadgeActionButton` adds a trailing button."],[424,"`bg-green-600`"],[441,"`bg-primary`"],[429,"`bg-subtle`"],[425,"`border-blue-700` etc."],[443,"`border-default`"],[430,"`border-subtle` etc."],[83,"`Breadcrumb`, `BreadcrumbLink`, and `BreadcrumbPage` render a `<nav>`, `<a>`, and `<span>`. Each accepts `asChild` and `className`."],[100,"`ButtonToolbar` combines multiple groups into a single toolbar."],[142,"`CardGroup` joins cards into an attached row."],[143,"`CardHeader`, `CardBody`, `CardFooter`, `CardTitle`, `CardSubtitle`, `CardText`, `CardImageOverlay`, and `CardGroup` are layout wrappers. Each accepts `asChild` and `className`."],[138,"`CardImage` places an image whose `position` controls which corners are rounded."],[139,"`CardImageOverlay` lays the `CardBody` over the image."],[170,"`Collapsible` lets users show and hide content with a trigger."],[490,"`DarkThemeToggle` switches between light and dark mode, persists the choice, and keeps all tabs in sync."],[207,"`DrawerBody` grows to fill the panel and scrolls its own overflow while the header stays pinned."],[221,"`DropdownMenuGroup` bundles related items under a `DropdownMenuLabel` section header."],[224,"`DropdownMenuItemText` displays non-interactive text in a menu."],[226,"`DropdownMenuItemText` renders non-interactive copy as a `<span>` and accepts a `className`."],[751,"`FormField`, `FormLabel`, `InputIcon`, `InputIconStart`, and `InputIconEnd` are\nlayout wrappers. Each accepts `asChild` and `className`."],[782,"`InputGroupText` is an addon wrapper. It accepts `asChild` and `className`."],[749,"`InputIcon` adds `InputIconStart` and/or `InputIconEnd` to an input while automatically adjusting the input padding."],[248,"`ListText` provides title and subtitle text for composing richer item layouts."],[300,"`NavbarBrand` and `NavbarText` are layout wrappers that accept only `asChild` and `className`. `NavbarTogglerIcon` renders the default hamburger glyph and accepts standard `svg` props."],[298,"`NavbarCollapse` wraps the Radix Collapsible content; for its shared props, see the Radix UI documentation."],[295,"`NavbarText` renders non-link content such as a signed-in label."],[291,"`NavbarToggle` and `NavbarCollapse` hide the menu behind a toggle below the `expand` breakpoint."],[299,"`NavbarToggle` wraps the Radix Collapsible trigger. For detailed usage guidelines, see the Radix UI documentation."],[270,"`NavItem` is a layout wrapper that accepts only `asChild` and `className`."],[594,"`p-(--my-padding)` — a custom CSS property"],[595,"`p-[12px]` — an arbitrary value"],[592,"`p-4` — a number, multiplied by the `--spacing` scale (where applicable)"],[593,"`p-px` — a fixed `1px` value"],[318,"`Pagination` is an accessible `<nav>` wrapping a `PaginationContent` list of `PaginationItem`s, with the current page marked by `active`."],[337,"`PopoverClose` dismisses the popover from within the content."],[340,"`PopoverHeader` and `PopoverBody` render the popover's header and body regions. Each accepts a `className`."],[797,"`RadioGroup` groups related radio buttons and manages the selected value."],[374,"`TableCaption` renders a caption above the table."],[375,"`TableFooter` renders a summary row group at the bottom of the table."],[376,"`TableHeader`, `TableBody`, `TableFooter`, `TableHead`, and `TableCaption` render their native table elements and accept only `className` alongside their standard element props."],[390,"`TabsList` uses the bordered style by default. Set `defaultValue` to select the initial tab."],[442,"`text-muted`"],[428,"`text-primary`"],[423,"`text-red-500`"],[472,"1\\. Custom dark mode selector"],[658,"1\\. Install Tailwind CSS"],[659,"2\\. Install Hummingbird React"],[473,"2\\. Set the initial theme"],[474,"3\\. Add a theme toggle"],[660,"3\\. Import CSS"],[661,"4\\. Use components"],[512,"A \"Reboot\" stylesheet (like Hummingbird's Reboot) resets browser styles and sets up a foundation for consistent design. Using CSS variables in Reboot makes it easy to customize base styles without editing the core CSS — just override the variables."],[780,"A `Button` can be placed alongside the form control as a trailing action."],[633,"A `Col` without any props creates equal-width columns for every screen size."],[243,"A `ListGroup` renders a vertical list of `ListGroupItem` elements."],[197,"A draggable, dismissible panel that slides in from any edge of the screen."],[231,"A flexible container for displaying a series of related content as a vertical list."],[127,"A flexible content container with header, body, and footer regions."],[329,"A floating panel anchored to a trigger, built on Radix Popover with Hummingbird's popover styling."],[714,"A label that floats above the control once it is focused or filled."],[494,"A list of theme variables that are overridden when dark mode is active."],[177,"A modal dialog built on Radix UI that traps focus, locks scroll, and dismisses on backdrop click or Escape."],[275,"A responsive navigation header with a brand, links, text, and a collapsible menu."],[381,"A set of layered panels whose triggers switch which panel is shown."],[53,"A small count or status descriptor for UI elements."],[400,"A small label that appears on hover or keyboard focus to describe the element beneath the pointer."],[696,"A styled native checkbox, including the indeterminate state."],[787,"A styled native radio button, with an optional group wrapper."],[756,"A styled native range slider for selecting a value from a range."],[805,"A styled native select for choosing one option from a list."],[253,"A styled navigation list of links with active and disabled states."],[345,"A styled table for displaying rows of data."],[823,"A toggle switch built on a native checkbox with role=\"switch\"."],[213,"A toggleable menu of actions or links, anchored to a trigger and positioned by Radix UI."],[2,"A vertically stacked set of interactive headings that each reveal a section of content."],[750,"Accepts the same `variant`, `size`, `color`, `state`, `asChild`, and `className` props as `FormControl`."],[1,"Accordion"],[234,"Actionable"],[437,"Actions colors (generate all color-related utilities)"],[258,"Active"],[354,"Active"],[233,"Active and disabled"],[394,"Add `disabled` to a `TabsTrigger` to prevent its panel from being selected."],[10,"Add `disabled` to an `AccordionItem` to prevent it from opening, or to the\n`Accordion` root to disable every item."],[506,"Address"],[15,"Alert"],[22,"Alert"],[23,"AlertIcon"],[610,"All breakpoints"],[458,"All components accept a `className` prop. Custom classes are merged with the component classes, so any Tailwind utility can be applied on top. For example, rounded pill buttons can be created by adding the `rounded-full` class."],[671,"All components accept a `className` prop. Custom classes are merged with the component classes, so Tailwind utility classes can be used to adjust any component."],[481,"All components rely on the same semantic tokens:"],[590,"All Tailwind utility classes can be applied to Hummingbird React components through the `className` prop. Custom classes are merged with the component classes, so utilities can adjust spacing, typography, radius, and more without writing custom CSS. This page lists the most frequently used utilities; see the official Tailwind CSS docs for the complete reference."],[515,"All the headings (`h1` to `h6`) in Hummingbird are styled with CSS variables for font size, weight, line height, and margin."],[279,"Always collapsed"],[43,"An avatar renders an image with a fallback for when the image is unavailable."],[148,"An icon-only button for dismissing content."],[33,"An image element with a text fallback for representing a user or entity."],[163,"An interactive component that expands and collapses a single panel of content."],[6,"API Reference"],[21,"API Reference"],[39,"API Reference"],[60,"API Reference"],[77,"API Reference"],[93,"API Reference"],[115,"API Reference"],[134,"API Reference"],[153,"API Reference"],[168,"API Reference"],[184,"API Reference"],[202,"API Reference"],[219,"API Reference"],[238,"API Reference"],[260,"API Reference"],[283,"API Reference"],[312,"API Reference"],[334,"API Reference"],[359,"API Reference"],[387,"API Reference"],[405,"API Reference"],[625,"API Reference"],[703,"API Reference"],[718,"API Reference"],[738,"API Reference"],[761,"API Reference"],[775,"API Reference"],[793,"API Reference"],[812,"API Reference"],[829,"API Reference"],[606,"Auto-layout columns"],[531,"Available themes"],[32,"Avatar"],[40,"Avatar"],[41,"AvatarGroup"],[575,"Background color utilities like `bg-highlight`, `bg-emphasis`, and many\nmore"],[434,"Background colors"],[52,"Badge"],[61,"Badge"],[62,"BadgeActionButton"],[605,"Basic example"],[432,"Behind the scenes, each semantic color class points to a CSS variable. Updating or overriding that variable updates the color everywhere it is used — including inside every Hummingbird React component."],[113,"Block button"],[507,"Blockquote"],[576,"Border color utilities like `border-default`, `border-subtle`, and many\nmore"],[436,"Border colors"],[589,"Border radius"],[350,"Bordered"],[351,"Borderless"],[73,"Breadcrumb"],[79,"BreadcrumbItem"],[78,"BreadcrumbList"],[632,"Breakpoint props allow easy sizing of columns without setting an explicit numbered span."],[535,"Breakpoints"],[104,"Button"],[87,"Button Group"],[111,"Button with icon"],[94,"ButtonGroup"],[501,"Buttons"],[105,"Buttons allow users to trigger an action or event with a single click. They are a core interactive element in any application interface."],[120,"Buttons come in three different sizes: `sm`, `md` (default), and `lg`."],[95,"ButtonToolbar"],[524,"By default, blockquotes (`<blockquote>`) have a bottom margin of `1r